title: Display property of item set to 'none' not taking effect in new PDF emitter
description: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, the item is still visible in the generated PDF. This is not the expected behavior.
OB: When the display property of an item is set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, the item should not be visible in the generated PDF.
EB: Upon previewing the PDF, the expected result is that the label should disappear. However, the actual result is that the label is still visible in the PDF.
SR: Please investigate and fix the issue with the display property not taking effect when set to 'none' in the new PDF emitter, so that the label disappears as expected in the generated PDF.
